summary: Requests & F.A.Q.
title: Requests & F.A.Q.
body:
So, I thought that this page will prove to be very helpful for future reference, and that’s why I decided to make it and compile it to one post because I think it’ll just be easier for the both of us. If you have any questions about the extent of my abilities and about myself, be sure to check this post before sending! Of course you are also free to shoot me any offbeat questions, I’m pretty open to anything.

How do I find my chart?

The most basic way you can find your chart is through the website cafeastrology. When I first got into astro, this was what I used, it’s extremely easy to read and beginner friendly. BUT I don’t wholly recommend it, I hope that once you’ve familiarised yourselves with reading the symbols and signs, you’ll use astro.com. They are more precise and correct, and their website offers a plethora of brief introduction articles.

Can I send you an ask on your main blog?

Yes and no. I don’t mind getting asks on my main blog about astrology, but I did create this blog for astrology, so I prefer getting them on this blog. I just don’t want to spam my followers on my main with Too Much astro that they didn’t exactly sign up for.

Can I send you my placements for compatibilities?

Sure. You can ask me who in BTS I think you’re compatible with, or how I think your relationship would be with specific members of your choice. Please send your Sun, Moon, Venus, Mercury, Mars and Rising. I am behind on compatibilities, so understand that I might answer late/selective with them.*

Can you do synastry chart reading?

Yes! I am open for this as well, but because this is more thorough, please understand that it will take longer for me to do. Also, I will only accept ONE member of your choice to do a chart with. Please send your date of birth, location and time. I am behind on compatibilities, so understand that I might answer late/selective with them.*

What kind of MTLs can you do?

Any! Like I said, I’m open to any questions, I’ve gotten asks from MTLs who in BTS are skilled in PowerPoint to who would most likely to be into BDSM lmao.

Can I request/ask something that’s not on this post?

Of course! Just shoot a message that’s astrology related. I am by no means an expert, but I’ll try to answer whatever question you have.

Why haven’t you responded to me in PM?

I’m horrible at replying via private messaging, I’m sorry. It’s hard to keep up with convos, so I’m sorry if I don’t reply! 

I don’t agree with what you said or astrology.

And that’s okay. I’m still an ever improving student, and I created this blog to broaden my spectrum, to go out of my comfort zone of only studying MY placements; I’m not as great as other astrologers on this website, and am aware. I am using a rumoured time of birth, and I know there are a lot of people who doesn’t think that’s proper since it could be misinformation. If you are not supportive of that, please let me know so I can make my posts more on the planets instead of the houses and risings. However, if you don’t agree with astrology, just don’t follow/visit this blog. This blog is strictly astrology related, and I know there are people who view astrology as something foolish. Astrology is a heavenly map of one’s identity that already pre-exists within themselves, it is about finding what’s already there, not trying to fit into stereotypical moulds of the signs. I am only translating and interpreting what the stars have written, my dudes, if you wanna argue about astrology’s validity, I don’t think I’m interested.
